-- Module 9, Lesson 3: Digital Product Launch Strategy
UPDATE lessons SET content = '<div class="lesson-content"><h2>Digital Product Launch Strategy</h2><h3>Launching Courses, Software, and Digital Products</h3><p>Digital product launches require different strategies than physical products or services. Building anticipation, creating urgency, and maximizing launch momentum drive success. This lesson provides a proven framework for digital product launches on Facebook.</p><h3>Pre-Launch Phase</h3><p>Build audience before launch. Create anticipation and buzz. Collect emails for launch list. Tease product benefits. Early bird offers. Countdown campaigns. Foundation for successful launch.</p><h3>Launch Sequence Timeline</h3><p>4-6 weeks pre-launch: Awareness. 2-3 weeks: Interest building. 1 week: Countdown. Launch day: Maximum push. Post-launch: Sustained promotion. Strategic timing maximizes impact.</p><h3>Audience Building</h3><p>Lead magnets related to product. Free content demonstrating expertise. Engagement campaigns. Video series. Build qualified audience. Email list critical for launch.</p><h3>Launch Campaign Structure</h3><p>Awareness: Introduce product and problem. Consideration: Demonstrate solution and value. Conversion: Launch offer and urgency. Retargeting: Follow up with interested. Layered approach maximizes conversions.</p><h3>Creative Strategy</h3><p>Product demo videos. Founder story and mission. Customer testimonials (if available). Feature highlights. Results and transformations. Compelling creative drives interest.</p><h3>Offer and Pricing</h3><p>Early bird discount. Launch bonuses. Limited-time pricing. Payment plans. Risk reversal (guarantee). Compelling offer drives action. Test different structures.</p><h3>Urgency and Scarcity</h3><p>Limited-time launch pricing. Enrollment deadline. Bonus expiration. Cart close. Authentic urgency converts. Avoid false scarcity.</p><h3>Launch Day Strategy</h3><p>Maximum ad spend. Email sequence. Social media push. Live events or webinars. All channels coordinated. Momentum creates momentum.</p><h3>Webinar Funnel</h3><p>Registration ads. Reminder sequence. Live presentation. Pitch and offer. Replay and follow-up. Proven model for digital products.</p><h3>Video Sales Letter (VSL)</h3><p>Long-form video presentation. Problem, solution, offer. Automated evergreen funnel. Scales beyond live launches. Test VSL vs webinar.</p><h3>Post-Launch Optimization</h3><p>Analyze launch performance. Identify what worked. Transition to evergreen. Sustained promotion strategy. Continuous improvement for future launches.</p><h3>Evergreen Funnel</h3><p>Automated ongoing sales. Simulated urgency. Consistent lead flow. Scales beyond launch events. Build sustainable business.</p><h3>Measurement and Goals</h3><p>Launch revenue target. Email list growth. Conversion rates. Cost per acquisition. Customer lifetime value. Clear goals enable evaluation.</p><h3>Common Launch Mistakes</h3><p>Insufficient audience building. Weak offer. Poor urgency. Inconsistent messaging. Technical issues. Inadequate follow-up. Learn from mistakes.</p><h3>Key Takeaways</h3><ul><li>Pre-launch audience building critical for success</li><li>Strategic timeline builds anticipation and momentum</li><li>Layered campaign structure from awareness to conversion</li><li>Compelling offer with authentic urgency drives action</li><li>Launch day maximum push across all channels</li><li>Webinar and VSL proven models for digital products</li><li>Transition to evergreen for sustained sales</li><li>Clear goals and measurement enable optimization</li></ul><p>Next lesson covers Agency Client Campaign Audit.</p></div>'
WHERE title = 'Digital Product Launch Strategy' AND EXISTS (
    SELECT 1 FROM modules m JOIN courses c ON m.course_id = c.id 
    WHERE m.id = lessons.module_id AND c.title LIKE '%Facebook%Ads%Mastery%'
);

-- Module 9, Lesson 4: Agency Client Campaign Audit
UPDATE lessons SET content = '<div class="lesson-content"><h2>Agency Client Campaign Audit</h2><h3>Professional Campaign Analysis and Recommendations</h3><p>Campaign audits identify optimization opportunities and demonstrate expertise. Whether for clients or your own accounts, systematic audits improve performance and build trust. This lesson provides a comprehensive framework for professional Facebook Ads audits.</p><h3>Audit Objectives</h3><p>Identify performance issues. Find optimization opportunities. Assess account health. Benchmark against best practices. Provide actionable recommendations. Demonstrate value. Build client confidence.</p><h3>Account Structure Review</h3><p>Campaign organization and naming. Ad set structure. Budget allocation. Objective alignment. Proper hierarchy. Clean structure enables optimization. Document structural issues.</p><h3>Targeting Analysis</h3><p>Audience selection appropriateness. Overlap and redundancy. Exclusion strategies. Audience size and saturation. Targeting efficiency. Identify targeting improvements.</p><h3>Creative Assessment</h3><p>Ad quality and relevance. Creative diversity. Refresh frequency. Message clarity. Visual appeal. Call-to-action strength. Creative drives performance.</p><h3>Performance Metrics Review</h3><p>KPI achievement vs goals. Efficiency metrics (CPA, ROAS). Engagement indicators. Trend analysis. Benchmark comparison. Identify performance gaps.</p><h3>Budget and Bidding</h3><p>Budget allocation strategy. Bidding approach appropriateness. CBO vs ABO usage. Spend efficiency. Scaling opportunities. Budget optimization potential.</p><h3>Conversion Tracking</h3><p>Pixel implementation. Event configuration. Attribution settings. Data accuracy. Tracking completeness. Proper tracking foundation for optimization.</p><h3>Landing Page Evaluation</h3><p>Page relevance to ads. User experience quality. Conversion optimization. Mobile responsiveness. Loading speed. Trust signals. Landing page impacts conversion rate.</p><h3>Compliance and Quality</h3><p>Policy compliance. Account quality score. Ad approval history. User feedback. Quality ranking. Compliance affects account health.</p><h3>Competitive Analysis</h3><p>Ad library research. Competitor strategies. Market positioning. Differentiation opportunities. Competitive intelligence informs strategy.</p><h3>Audit Report Structure</h3><p>Executive summary. Current performance overview. Key findings and issues. Prioritized recommendations. Implementation roadmap. Expected impact. Professional presentation.</p><h3>Prioritizing Recommendations</h3><p>Quick wins first. High-impact opportunities. Resource requirements. Implementation difficulty. Prioritization helps clients act. Focus on actionable items.</p><h3>Presenting Audit Results</h3><p>Clear, jargon-free language. Visual data presentation. Specific examples. Actionable recommendations. Positive and constructive tone. Professional delivery builds trust.</p><h3>Implementation Planning</h3><p>Phased approach. Timeline and milestones. Resource requirements. Success metrics. Accountability. Clear plan enables execution.</p><h3>Follow-Up and Monitoring</h3><p>Track implementation progress. Measure impact of changes. Ongoing optimization. Regular check-ins. Continuous improvement. Audits start process, not end it.</p><h3>Key Takeaways</h3><ul><li>Systematic audits identify optimization opportunities</li><li>Review account structure, targeting, creative, performance</li><li>Assess conversion tracking and landing pages</li><li>Benchmark against best practices and competitors</li><li>Prioritize recommendations by impact and ease</li><li>Professional report with clear, actionable insights</li><li>Implementation planning critical for results</li><li>Follow-up ensures recommendations drive improvement</li></ul><p>Next lesson covers Building a Portfolio for Freelance Work.</p></div>'
WHERE title = 'Agency Client Campaign Audit' AND EXISTS (
    SELECT 1 FROM modules m JOIN courses c ON m.course_id = c.id 
    WHERE m.id = lessons.module_id AND c.title LIKE '%Facebook%Ads%Mastery%'
);

