-- Module 10, Lesson 5: Landing Clients & Pricing Your Services
UPDATE lessons SET content = '<div class="lesson-content"><h2>Landing Clients & Pricing Your Services</h2><h3>Building a Profitable Facebook Ads Business</h3><p>Attracting clients and pricing services appropriately determines business success. Strategic client acquisition and value-based pricing maximize income and sustainability. This final lesson provides practical strategies for landing clients and pricing your Facebook Ads services profitably.</p><h3>Client Acquisition Channels</h3><p>Referrals and word-of-mouth. Content marketing and SEO. LinkedIn outreach. Networking events. Freelance platforms. Paid advertising. Email outreach. Multiple channels reduce risk.</p><h3>Ideal Client Profile</h3><p>Industry and business size. Budget capacity. Growth stage. Values alignment. Communication style. Define ideal client. Focus attracts right fit.</p><h3>Outreach Strategies</h3><p>Personalized LinkedIn messages. Value-first approach. Specific insights or ideas. No hard selling initially. Build relationship. Consultative approach. Quality over quantity.</p><h3>Proposal Development</h3><p>Understand client needs first. Customized solutions. Clear deliverables. Timeline and process. Pricing options. Terms and conditions. Professional proposals close deals.</p><h3>Pricing Models</h3><p>Hourly rates. Monthly retainers. Project-based fees. Performance-based compensation. Hybrid models. Choose based on service and client. Multiple models possible.</p><h3>Hourly Rate Pricing</h3><p>Simple and flexible. $50-200+ per hour typical. Track time carefully. Caps or estimates recommended. Good for consulting. Transparent but limits income.</p><h3>Monthly Retainer</h3><p>Recurring revenue. Predictable income. Ongoing relationship. $1000-10000+ monthly. Most common for management. Sustainable business model.</p><h3>Project-Based Fees</h3><p>Fixed price for scope. Audits, setups, launches. Clear deliverables. $2000-20000+ per project. Defined beginning and end. Good for specific services.</p><h3>Performance-Based Pricing</h3><p>Percentage of ad spend or revenue. Aligns incentives. Higher risk and reward. 10-20% of ad spend typical. Requires trust and tracking. Advanced pricing model.</p><h3>Value-Based Pricing</h3><p>Price based on client value received. Not time invested. Higher rates for higher value. Requires confidence and positioning. Most profitable approach. Communicate value clearly.</p><h3>Setting Your Rates</h3><p>Calculate costs and desired income. Research market rates. Consider experience level. Factor in value provided. Confidence in pricing. Start conservative, increase with experience.</p><h3>Presenting Pricing</h3><p>Confidence and clarity. Options and packages. Value justification. Investment framing, not cost. Address objections proactively. Professional presentation.</p><h3>Handling Objections</h3><p>Listen and understand concern. Reframe value proposition. Offer alternatives or payment plans. Know when to walk away. Not every prospect right fit. Confidence attracts clients.</p><h3>Contracts and Agreements</h3><p>Clear scope and deliverables. Payment terms. Cancellation policy. Intellectual property. Confidentiality. Legal protection. Professional contracts essential.</p><h3>Scaling Client Acquisition</h3><p>Systematize outreach. Referral programs. Content marketing. Strategic partnerships. Team building. Automation where appropriate. Scale sustainably.</p><h3>Client Retention</h3><p>Deliver results consistently. Communicate proactively. Exceed expectations. Build relationships. Continuous optimization. Retention easier than acquisition. Focus on success.</p><h3>Key Takeaways</h3><ul><li>Multiple client acquisition channels reduce dependency</li><li>Define ideal client profile to focus efforts</li><li>Value-first outreach builds relationships</li><li>Pricing models: hourly, retainer, project, performance-based</li><li>Value-based pricing most profitable long-term</li><li>Set rates based on value provided, not just time</li><li>Present pricing confidently with clear value justification</li><li>Client retention through results and relationships</li></ul><p>Congratulations on completing Facebook Ads Mastery! Apply these strategies to build a successful Facebook advertising career or business.</p></div>'
WHERE title = 'Landing Clients & Pricing Your Services' AND EXISTS (
    SELECT 1 FROM modules m JOIN courses c ON m.course_id = c.id 
    WHERE m.id = lessons.module_id AND c.title LIKE '%Facebook%Ads%Mastery%'
